1
00:00:04,637 --> 00:00:08,608
So Geonwoo, what does success mean to you?

2
00:00:10,110 --> 00:00:13,680
When I was a kid, it was being on TV.

3
00:00:14,447 --> 00:00:17,416
It felt like the whole world was inside.

4
00:00:17,417 --> 00:00:20,587
Then it was doing commercials,

5
00:00:21,087 --> 00:00:24,257
and as I got older, starring in a drama,

6
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:29,129
winning awards, and so on.

7
00:00:30,163 --> 00:00:32,664
The bar just kept getting higher.

8
00:00:32,665 --> 00:00:33,633
Yeah.

9
00:00:33,634 --> 00:00:36,169
But lately, I'm not so sure.

10
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:38,604
When my insomnia is really bad,

11
00:00:38,605 --> 00:00:42,041
just getting a good night's
sleep feels like success.

12
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:43,375
When I'm on a strict diet,

13
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:46,079
being able to eat whatever
I want feels like a win.

14
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,248
My definition of success

15
00:00:49,249 --> 00:00:51,951
is always changing.

16
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:58,958
So, what's the hardest part
about being in this industry?

17
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:05,498
Always having to smile in front of people.

18
00:01:06,766 --> 00:01:09,935
Even when I'm falling apart inside,

19
00:01:09,936 --> 00:01:12,605
no one can really tell.

20
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,975
That's the hard part.

21
00:01:27,153 --> 00:01:30,457
Can you check if I look okay?

22
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,340
Uh... do I look alright?

23
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:51,010
Is that really so important?

24
00:02:13,266 --> 00:02:15,969
I've always wondered something.

25
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:17,537
Huh?

26
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:22,442
When did you and Taewoo get so close?

27
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:27,713
We first met at a local gym.

28
00:02:27,714 --> 00:02:30,182
Taewoo was pretty shy back then,

29
00:02:30,183 --> 00:02:32,118
so I looked out for him.

30
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:38,290
You might already know this,

31
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:40,259
but when I was a kid,

32
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:42,194
back when I was a child actor,

33
00:02:42,195 --> 00:02:46,266
there was a scene
where I had to get in a car.

34
00:02:47,534 --> 00:02:50,370
I was actually kidnapped that time.

35
00:02:50,403 --> 00:02:52,070
Kidnapped?

36
00:02:52,071 --> 00:02:53,372
Yeah.

37
00:02:53,373 --> 00:02:56,643
People said I was unusually calm.

38
00:02:58,077 --> 00:02:59,411
When I got out of the car,

39
00:02:59,412 --> 00:03:00,946
I didn't even cry.

40
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:02,849
I seemed totally fine.

41
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:05,918
That's because

42
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:08,188
the person who took me

43
00:03:08,621 --> 00:03:10,590
was my father.

44
00:03:12,892 --> 00:03:15,594
We started filming and got in the car.

45
00:03:15,595 --> 00:03:18,397
My dad was in the driver's seat.

46
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:22,202
I was so excited, asking
where we were going.

47
00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:26,271
But my dad...

48
00:03:26,272 --> 00:03:30,510
just kept crying and saying he was sorry.

49
00:03:31,578 --> 00:03:34,646
He took me to a toy store,

50
00:03:34,647 --> 00:03:37,082
bought me a robot,

51
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:39,052
and then he just left.

52
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:43,021
It never made the news.

53
00:03:43,022 --> 00:03:45,057
Only my mom, my manager,

54
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,126
and I knew about it.

55
00:03:47,827 --> 00:03:50,496
I really didn't want the world to know.

56
00:03:50,797 --> 00:03:52,432
But...

57
00:03:53,933 --> 00:03:56,835
is it okay that

58
00:03:56,836 --> 00:03:58,838
you're telling me this?

59
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:02,141
Yeah.

60
00:04:02,442 --> 00:04:05,511
I just needed someone to talk to.

61
00:04:06,212 --> 00:04:11,150
For some reason, I
felt like I could trust you.

62
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:17,790
Hyung, what are you talking about?

63
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,795
So you don't trust me?

64
00:04:23,796 --> 00:04:27,700
You knew I hated you, yet
you still kept this from me?

65
00:04:28,534 --> 00:04:29,369
Taewoo, it's not like that...

66
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:31,070
Not like that?

67
00:04:31,838 --> 00:04:33,138
You know

68
00:04:33,139 --> 00:04:35,241
I've always been the odd one out.

69
00:04:36,242 --> 00:04:38,477
To everyone else, I'm just
Geonwoo's little brother.

70
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:41,748
Even the stuff about
Dad only belongs to you.

71
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:46,386
I knew you felt left out.

72
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,187
That's why I couldn't tell you.

73
00:04:49,188 --> 00:04:51,156
If you had known about Dad too,

74
00:04:51,157 --> 00:04:52,224
it would've hurt you even more.

75
00:04:52,225 --> 00:04:53,358
Stop making excuses!

76
00:04:53,359 --> 00:04:55,727
That's my business too.

77
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:57,663
You just made me look like a fool.

78
00:04:57,664 --> 00:04:59,432
That's enough.

79
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:02,602
Let's calm down before we talk.

80
00:05:03,736 --> 00:05:05,271
Jaeyeon...

81
00:05:05,571 --> 00:05:07,939
You said you'd always be on my side.

82
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:09,441
Taewoo.

83
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:11,910
I'm not taking sides here.

84
00:05:11,911 --> 00:05:13,478
Taewoo, don't be like this.

85
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:15,347
This isn't Jaeyeon's fault.

86
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:16,515
Enough.

87
00:05:16,516 --> 00:05:18,216
I get it now.

88
00:05:18,217 --> 00:05:20,286
In the end, I'm always second best.

89
00:05:20,887 --> 00:05:22,889
Taewoo!

90
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:31,531
Let go of my hand.

91
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,032
I'll be right back.

92
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:37,036
I'll go talk to Taewoo and come back.

93
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:40,073
Please wait for me here.

94
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:54,687
Taewoo!

95
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:01,360
Hey, where are you going?

96
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:02,961
What am I supposed to do?

97
00:06:02,962 --> 00:06:05,230
What am I supposed to do staying here?

98
00:06:05,231 --> 00:06:06,665
Don't run.

99
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,868
I'm right here.

100
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:12,605
Let's go together, okay?

101
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:17,243
Come on.

102
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:27,787
Taewoo...

103
00:06:28,187 --> 00:06:29,588
Stop drinking so much.

104
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:30,789
Huh?

105
00:06:30,790 --> 00:06:32,658
About your brother...

106
00:06:33,292 --> 00:06:35,427
Jaeyeon...

107
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:37,430
I know.

108
00:06:38,331 --> 00:06:40,666
I know he's hurting too.

109
00:06:43,536 --> 00:06:46,738
He's been on set since he was a kid.

110
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:48,841
He barely even went to school.

111
00:06:49,475 --> 00:06:52,211
He doesn't really have any friends.

112
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:54,813
I know.

113
00:06:54,814 --> 00:06:57,083
I know I've just been blaming him.

114
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,418
I know...

115
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,386
Taewoo...

116
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:03,789
You were just a kid back then, too.

117
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,090
We're still young.

118
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,026
We're only in our twenties.

119
00:07:07,326 --> 00:07:10,930
Let's just consider this part
of the healing process, okay?

120
00:07:11,497 --> 00:07:13,466
I feel so bad for my brother.

121
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,003
I had no idea back then.

122
00:07:18,237 --> 00:07:20,606
I just really missed my dad.

123
00:07:21,674 --> 00:07:25,111
I hate that I'm like this.

124
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:30,583
Looking back...

125
00:07:31,517 --> 00:07:34,019
I'm really glad I have you.

126
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,588
Jaeyeon...

127
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:39,958
If I didn't have you,

128
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:42,395
I don't think I would've made it this far.

129
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:17,763
Man... you're so heavy.

130
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:45,424
Finally...

131
00:09:01,841 --> 00:09:04,143
Don't go.

132
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:16,856
This isn't right...

133
00:09:24,597 --> 00:09:26,699
Goodbye...

134
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,700
"Fan Service"
(Episode 4)

